## Template Validation

**When Creating Skills:**
```bash
# Validate SKILL.md
- [ ] YAML frontmatter present and valid
- [ ] Name matches directory name
- [ ] Type is valid (Discipline, Technique, Pattern, Reference)
- [ ] CSO score calculated and documented
- [ ] Progressive disclosure (≤200 lines main file)
- [ ] References/ directory exists (if needed)
- [ ] Examples provided (minimum 3)
```

**When Creating Agents:**
```bash
# Validate agent.md
- [ ] YAML frontmatter present and valid
- [ ] Tool tier appropriate (read_only for validators)
- [ ] Description clear and concise
- [ ] Usage examples provided
- [ ] Tool restrictions documented
```

**When Creating Commands:**
```bash
# Validate command.md
- [ ] YAML frontmatter present and valid
- [ ] Workflow type matches actual pattern
- [ ] User-facing prompts clear
- [ ] Error handling specified
- [ ] Examples provided
```

