## Meta-Infrastructure Anti-Patterns

**❌ Avoid:**
- Bloated SKILL.md (>200 lines without references/)
- Missing YAML frontmatter
- Low CSO scores without justification
- Wrong tool tier (full access for validators)
- Inconsistent naming (camelCase, snake_case)
- No examples
- Duplication across components

**✅ Prefer:**
- Progressive disclosure (main file + references/)
- Complete YAML frontmatter
- CSO scores meeting targets (≥0.7 or ≥0.8)
- Appropriate tool tiers (read_only for validators)
- Consistent kebab-case naming
- Comprehensive examples (3-5 minimum)
- DRY principle (reference, don't duplicate)

---

## Quality Gates

**Before Committing .claude/ Changes:**
1. Run System Coherence Validator (when available)
2. Verify YAML frontmatter valid
3. Check CSO score meets target
4. Ensure naming conventions followed
5. Validate file structure (SKILL.md + references/ + templates/)
6. Test auto-invoke (if applicable)

